The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Victory for England 
                                                                                                                       7                                      Victory for England 
                      
	Nottingham: Bangladesh captain Mashrafe Mortaza admitted he faced a severe test of his leadership capabilities after the Tigers latest loss was compounded by injuries to two key players.         
	England cruised to a six-wicket win in the first ODI as Bangladesh, yet to win in 2010, were well beaten at Trent Bridge in a day-night contest here Thursday.         
	To make matters worse for Bangladesh, both wicket-keeper Mushfiqur Rahim and batsman Raqibul Hasan were ruled out of the remaining two games of the series.           (AGENCIES)                                                                                                                 
